           <h2> Confidence equals conversions.</h2> 
            <p>
            Your digital business is built on trust, and you can&rsquo;t close the
            deal with an unsecured website. Customers won&rsquo;t fill out a form–or
            fill up a shopping cart–until they know their personal information
            is safe. 
            </p>
            <p>
            An SSL certificate from Media Temple is the easy, affordable way
            to secure your site and give your business a boost.
            
            <a href="https://ac.mediatemple.net/services/add/server/index.mt?act=ssl">Log
            in to get started »</a>
            <p>
        </div>
        <div id='content-div-faq'>
        <h1>FAQ</h1>
            <div class="faq-cell top left">
                <div>
                    <strong>
                        What kind of SSL Certificate do you offer?
                    </strong>
                    <p class='no-margin'>
                        We currently offer a GeoTrust QuickSSL certificate, the simplest and most common type of GeoTrust SSL certificate. It offers a balance of features and ease of use that&rsquo;s just right for most of our customers, including:
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Over 99% browser compatibility, plus most mobile device browsers
                        </li>
                        <li>
                        Strong 256-bit encryption and 2048-bit root
                        </li>
                        <li>
                        Automatic authentication and issuance in just minutes
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-cell top right">
                <div>
                    <strong>
                        What are the benefits of an SSL?
                    </strong>
                    <p>
    There are two main benefits: First, it acts like an online ID card, proving that your site has been verified by a certificate authority. Second, it creates a secure, encrypted connection (a Secure Sockets Layer) between your web server and visitors&rsquo; browsers, ensuring that any information they send can&rsquo;t be seen or read by anyone else. Which ultimately means your customers will feel a lot more comfortable doing business with you, because they know that their personal information is in good hands. 
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-cell bottom left">
                <div>
                    <strong>
                        How do I install it?
                    </strong>
                    <p>
                        For most (mt) services, we have AccountCenter tools
                        that install SSL certificates automatically. If
                        you&rsquo;re not eligible for automatic installation,
                        or if you&rsquo;d rather do it yourself, please see <a href='http://kb.mediatemple.net/questions/430/Installing+an+SSL+Certificate' target='new_window'>this KnowledgeBase article</a> for easy, step by step instructions.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-cell bottom right">
                <div>
                    <strong>
                        Can I get a security seal on my website?
                    </strong>
                    <p>
                        Yes. Our certificates are compatible with the GeoTrust
                        True Site Seal. Find instructions for installing the
                        seal <a href='http://www.geotrust.com/support/quick-ssl-support/premium-true-site-seal/index.html' target='new_window'>here</a>. 
                    </p>
                    <strong>
                        Can anyone purchase an SSL?
                    </strong>
                    <p>
                        Yes, anyone with a current (mt) account can purchase an SSL certificate from us.
                    <p>
                </div>
            </div>
